This apartment (G05) is quite tired and the bathrooms are in need of a good clean. Our washing machine didn’t spin and our load of washing was stuck inside overnight until management had their handyman take a look the next day. The handyman was helpful but of course the main issue is how long we went without a washing machine - 1/2 days. With 3 kids, beach towels etc it made the trip restricted. I did contemplate going to a laundromat but this is another expense and also time away from the kids. 

The lounge room pleather couch was worn down, surface was cracked and it was also very uncomfortable when turned into a bed. The apartment was also extremely dark, the only natural light coming from the outdoor area - which was more like a concrete box without a roof. I had lights on the entire time. 

The beds were a positive, king sized, clean and nice comfortable pillows. Kitchen was well stocked with all you’d need, also plenty of coffee/tea and even plentiful coffee biscuits which was a nice addition. 

The location is also good, we ate at one of the laneway bars only 20mts from the gate, with the kids and it was lovely under the fairy lights. 

Parking is $20 a night but we opted to use st parking. Should be noted st parking is $4/hr (9-5pm and 9-12 sat) - surprisingly high for Newcastle! So bc we were in and out all day it worked out better to just pay the hour rate when needed but if you’re wanting to leave the car for most of the day you’re best off paying the $20. 

All in all it was a satisfactory stay however I wouldn’t return based on the lack of up keep of the property.
